{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75c42501-89f0-48ed-a1c2-43d4db7a590b","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8ad12e05-7323-4035-aeab-bdcac096d914","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about the dotnet CLI - I can answer directly without needing to explore files.","outputTokens":166,"requestId":"A043:834FC:CDEF8E:F28EB6:69FE8D5C"},"id":"8e2011a1-e99b-4940-bfab-7583e01d42bc","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:26:56.991Z","parentId":"45ab6b22-740a-4e08-821c-152476fbd7f8"}
